column1: #Text=I do n't really think of myself as a born-again , and they of course insist on later baptism .
#Text=I 'm sort of currently leaning towards the Baptist church .
#Text=DS : They 're one of the least intolerant .
#Text=I do n't know ; I have n't decided --
#Text=DS : I went through a Southern Baptist phase when I lived in Georgia .
#Text=The Southern Baptist convention is probably the most conservative out there .
#Text=DS : If you were forced to choose , which war would you prefer to fight in , Iraq or Afghanistan ?
#Text=JR : Which one would I rather fight in ?
#Text=DS : On the side of the United States .
#Text=JR : Well , at least we had an endgame .
#Text=My reasoning is completely ridiculous : I distrust men who are that skinny .
#Text=You and I are both lean , but if I told you , you 've got to go take this stump out to the backyard , and I gave you an axe , I 'd be pretty confident you could do it .
#Text=Obama does n't look like he could do it to me .
#Text=DS : If you remain that lean on the campaign trail , when they 're having all those --
#Text=There 's something about it I distrust , a guy who ca n't lift a hammer .
#Text=DS : How would you choose to die ?
#Text=JR : How would I choose to die ?
#Text=Most men stop being afraid of dying .
#Text=Then , when they have kids , suddenly they 're afraid of it again .
#Text=But not for themselves , for their kids .
#Text=So I do n't really care , just as long as my kids are provided for .
#Text=DS : You think that most men , pre-parenthood , lose their sense of mortality and their fear of it ?
#Text=JR : I think you just get tired of being afraid of it .
#Text=DS : Were you ever afraid of it ?
#Text=JR : Yeah , I was afraid of it in my early twenties ; and as a kid , I just remember being really , really afraid of dying , and it being incomprehensible and depressing .
#Text=We had a lizard die , and that was a big deal .
#Text=She was asking these questions , " Is it gonna be another lizard ?
